00:03:48.209 --> 00:03:54.459
is not based on money, we find that people
actually don't barter at all. So David Graeber's

00:03:54.459 --> 00:03:59.430
book "Debt: The First 5,000 Years" surveys
the literature of anthropology and discovers

00:03:59.430 --> 00:04:04.530
that in societies without money, people don't
actually barter, but they do find ways to

00:04:04.530 --> 00:04:09.250
exchange. He quotes an anthropologist named
Caroline Humphrey, who concluded: "No example

00:04:09.250 --> 00:04:14.200
of a barter economy, pure and simple, has
ever been described, let alone the emergence

00:04:14.200 --> 00:04:19.769
from it of money; all available ethnography
suggests that there has never been such a

00:04:19.769 --> 00:04:19.980
thing."

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:23.350
Now, that's not to say that barter doesn't
